The proposed framework involves the use of structured probabilistic models and deep networks, which are commonly used in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) research. Therefore, cs.CV, cs.LG, and cs.AI are all likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of auto-encoders, which are a type of neural network commonly used in unsupervised learning. This suggests that cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing) may also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of datasets involving moving objects, which suggests that cs.MM (multimedia) may also be a relevant sub-category.
